The 58-year-old from Staten Island, New York, said: 'I started creating sand sculptures with my kids about 18 years ago while we were on vacation.

'I saw someone create something in the sand, and I thought, "gee, I can do this."

'These days I don't really create sand castles - what I do is make people smile and that's become it for me.'

His work has taken him across the world where he builds sculptures for private parties, events and corporations.

The fairy palace features a staircase wrapping around a high tower supported by intricate arches - made only of sand and water.

It is so detailed, individual 'bricks' are visible and passersby can see every tiny window. 

Mr Long, who has placed in world championship sand sculpting competitions, was built to showcase his talents.

